headline: Colbert Says CBS Blocked Appearance by Democratic Candidate
summary: Speaking on Monday night Colbert said the lawyers informed his team that state Representative James Talarico couldn’t appear on the broadcast and his name shouldn’t be mentioned.  “He was supposed to be here, but we were told in no uncertain terms by our network’s lawyers, who called us directly, that we could not have him on the broadcast,” Colbert said.  In a statement, CBS denied barring the candidate’s interview, saying the show was only told that Talarico’s appearance could set in motion a Federal Communications Commission requirement that his opponents also be allowed to appear.

headline: Disney Lawsuit Against ByteDance Puts AI And IP Value In Focus
summary: Disney (NYSE:DIS) has escalated legal action against ByteDance over the alleged unauthorized use of its intellectual property. The dispute centers on ByteDance’s Seedance 2.0 AI video generator and its use of Disney owned characters and content. The case highlights growing tensions around copyright and data use in AI powered media tools.
